results.name: Prime numbers arising in A066071.
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: Solutions to 1+phi(x)=13 are {13, 21, 26, 28, 36, 42}; so 13 occur 5 times in the sequence in positions 10, 13, 15, 18 and 21, obtained as 1+Phi[m] values for 5 composite arguments.
mathematica: Select[EulerPhi@ # + 1 & /@ Complement[Range@ #, Prime@ Range@ PrimePi@ #] &@ 168, PrimeQ] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Jul 01 2016 *)
program: (PARI) { n=0; for (m=1, 10^9, if (!isprime(m) && isprime(p=(eulerphi(m) + 1)), write("b066072.txt", n++, " ", p); if (n==1000, return)) ) } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Nov 10 2009
